 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Day 4: Advanced RAG – Optimization & Context\n",
    "\n",
    "**Objective:** Optimize retrieval quality and learn to measure RAG performance systematically.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Topics:**\n",
    "- Hybrid search (vector + keyword) using Pinecone\n",
    "- Re-ranking retrieved chunks with a cross-encoder (Cohere or HuggingFace)\n",
    "- RAG evaluation metrics: faithfulness, answer relevance, context recall\n",
    "- Prompt engineering for better answers\n",
    "\n",
    "> 💡 **Memory aid**: Good retrieval is not enough; you must measure and improve. Today we add evaluation and re-ranking to your RAG pipeline."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Setup & Imports"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from dotenv import load_dotenv\n",
    "import pinecone\n",
    "from langchain.embeddings import OpenAIEmbeddings\n",
    "from langchain.vectorstores import Pinecone as LangChainPinecone\n",
    "from langchain.chat_models import ChatOpenAI\n",
    "from langchain.schema import Document\n",
    "from typing import List, Tuple\n",
    "import time\n",
    "\n",
    "load_dotenv()\n",
    "\n",
    "pinecone_api_key = os.getenv(\"PINECONE_API_KEY\")\n",
    "openai_api_key = os.getenv(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Environment loaded.\")\n",
    "if not pinecone_api_key or not openai_api_key:\n",
    "    print(\"⚠️ Missing API keys. Please set PINECONE_API_KEY and OPENAI_API_KEY in .env\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Load Existing Vector Store (from Day 3)\n",
    "\n",
    "We assume you completed Day 3 and have an index named `rag-workshop` with your financial documents."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize Pinecone and embeddings\n",
    "pc = pinecone.Pinecone(api_key=pinecone_api_key)\n",
    "index_name = \"rag-workshop\"\n",
    "embeddings = OpenAIEmbeddings(model=\"text-embedding-ada-002\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Connect to existing vector store\n",
    "vector_store = LangChainPinecone.from_existing_index(\n",
    "    index_name=index_name,\n",
    "    embedding=embeddings\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(f\"Connected to Pinecone index '{index_name}'\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Hybrid Search (Vector + Keyword)\n",
    "\n",
    "Pinecone supports hybrid search by combining dense vectors (semantic) with sparse vectors (keyword matching using BM25). We'll implement it using the Pinecone Python client directly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Helper function for hybrid search\n",
    "def hybrid_search(query: str, top_k: int = 3, alpha: float = 0.5) -> List[Tuple[Document, float]]:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Hybrid search: alpha=0 -> pure keyword, alpha=1 -> pure vector\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    # Generate dense vector embedding\n",
    "    dense_vec = embeddings.embed_query(query)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Generate sparse vector (BM25) - we'll use Pinecone's built-in sparse embedding\n",
    "    # For simplicity, we create a dummy sparse vector; in production use pinecone.SparseVector\n",
    "    from pinecone import SparseVector\n",
    "    # Pinecone requires precomputed sparse vectors; we'll simulate by using metadata filtering\n",
    "    # Actually, we need to upsert with sparse vectors first. This is a demonstration.\n",
    "    # For a complete implementation, see: https://docs.pinecone.io/docs/hybrid-search\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # For now, let's fall back to simple dense search with note\n",
    "    print(\"Hybrid search requires pre-computed sparse vectors during upsert.\")\n",
    "    print(\"We'll demonstrate with dense + metadata filtering as approximation.\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Dense search\n",
    "    results = vector_store.similarity_search_with_score(query, k=top_k)\n",
    "    return results\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test\n",
    "query = \"capital adequacy ratio Basel III\"\n",
    "results = hybrid_search(query, top_k=2)\n",
    "for doc, score in results:\n",
    "    print(f\"Score: {score:.3f} - {doc.page_content[:150]}...\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Note:** For true hybrid search, you need to upsert both dense and sparse vectors. See the [Pinecone hybrid search guide](https://docs.pinecone.io/docs/hybrid-search). We'll use dense search for the rest of the day."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Re-ranking Retrieved Chunks\n",
    "\n",
    "A cross-encoder (like Cohere or a HuggingFace model) evaluates each (query, chunk) pair and assigns a relevance score, reordering chunks better than pure vector similarity."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Option 1: Using HuggingFace cross-encoder (free, no API key)\n",
    "from sentence_transformers import CrossEncoder\n",
    "\n",
    "cross_encoder = CrossEncoder('cross-encoder/ms-marco-MiniLM-L-6-v2')\n",
    "\n",
    "def rerank_with_crossencoder(query: str, documents: List[Document], top_k: int = 2) -> List[Document]:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Re-rank documents using cross-encoder\"\"\"\n",
    "    pairs = [(query, doc.page_content) for doc in documents]\n",
    "    scores = cross_encoder.predict(pairs)\n",
    "    # Sort documents by score descending\n",
    "    scored_docs = sorted(zip(documents, scores), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\n",
    "    return [doc for doc, score in scored_docs[:top_k]]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test: retrieve more chunks than needed, then re-rank\n",
    "query = \"What is SOC 2?\"\n",
    "initial_docs = vector_store.similarity_search(query, k=5)\n",
    "reranked_docs = rerank_with_crossencoder(query, initial_docs, top_k=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Original top chunk:\")\n",
    "print(initial_docs[0].page_content[:200])\n",
    "print(\"\\nRe-ranked top chunk:\")\n",
    "print(reranked_docs[0].page_content[:200])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Option 2: Using Cohere API (requires COHERE_API_KEY)\n",
    "# from langchain.rerankers import CohereRerank\n",
    "# reranker = CohereRerank(model=\"rerank-english-v3.0\")\n",
    "# reranked = reranker.rerank(query, documents=initial_docs, top_n=2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. RAG Evaluation Metrics\n",
    "\n",
    "We'll evaluate three core metrics:\n",
    "- **Faithfulness**: Does the answer stay true to the retrieved context? (no hallucinations)\n",
    "- **Answer Relevance**: Does the answer address the question?\n",
    "- **Context Recall**: Was all necessary information retrieved?\n",
    "\n",
    "We'll use the `ragas` library (install with `pip install ragas`)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install if needed (uncomment)\n",
    "# !pip install ragas -q\n",
    "\n",
    "from ragas import evaluate\n",
    "from ragas.metrics import faithfulness, answer_relevancy, context_recall\n",
    "from datasets import Dataset\n",
    "import pandas as pd"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Create a Test Set\n",
    "\n",
    "We'll define a few questions, retrieve contexts, generate answers with an LLM, then evaluate."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Setup LLM for answer generation\n",
    "llm = ChatOpenAI(model=\"gpt-3.5-turbo\", temperature=0.2)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sample questions and ground truth (simplified)\n",
    "test_questions = [\n",
    "    \"What is the minimum CET1 capital ratio under Basel III?\",\n",
    "    \"What does GDPR Article 17 cover?\",\n",
    "    \"What are the five trust service criteria in SOC 2?\"\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Retrieve contexts\n",
    "contexts_list = []\n",
    "answers = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for q in test_questions:\n",
    "    docs = vector_store.similarity_search(q, k=3)\n",
    "    contexts = [doc.page_content for doc in docs]\n",
    "    contexts_list.append(contexts)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Generate answer\n",
    "    prompt = f\"Answer the question based only on the following context. If the answer is not in the context, say 'Not found'.\\n\\nContext: {' '.join(contexts)}\\n\\nQuestion: {q}\\nAnswer:\"\n",
    "    response = llm.predict(prompt)\n",
    "    answers.append(response)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a dataset in Ragas format\n",
    "data = {\n",
    "    \"question\": test_questions,\n",
    "    \"answer\": answers,\n",
    "    \"contexts\": contexts_list,\n",
    "    \"ground_truth\": [\n",
    "        \"4.5%\",\n",
    "        \"Right to erasure (right to be forgotten)\",\n",
    "        \"Security, availability, processing integrity, confidentiality, privacy\"\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "}\n",
    "dataset = Dataset.from_dict(data)\n",
    "dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Run Evaluation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "result = evaluate(\n",
    "    dataset,\n",
    "    metrics=[faithfulness, answer_relevancy, context_recall]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert to DataFrame for easy viewing\n",
    "df_result = pd.DataFrame([result])\n",
    "print(\"Evaluation Results:\")\n",
    "df_result"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# View per-sample scores\n",
    "for i, q in enumerate(test_questions):\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nQuestion {i+1}: {q}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Answer: {answers[i][:150]}...\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Faithfulness: {result['faithfulness'][i]:.2f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Answer Relevancy: {result['answer_relevancy'][i]:.2f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Context Recall: {result['context_recall'][i]:.2f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Prompt Engineering for RAG\n",
    "\n",
    "The prompt you feed to the LLM dramatically affects answer quality. Let's experiment with different prompt styles."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "query = \"What is GDPR?\"\n",
    "context_docs = vector_store.similarity_search(query, k=1)\n",
    "context = context_docs[0].page_content\n",
    "\n",
    "# Different prompt templates\n",
    "prompts = {\n",
    "    \"Basic\": f\"Context: {context}\\nQuestion: {query}\\nAnswer:\",\n",
    "    \"Instruction\": f\"You are a compliance expert. Using only the context below, answer the question accurately. If uncertain, say 'I don't know'.\\n\\nContext: {context}\\nQuestion: {query}\\nAnswer:\",\n",
    "    \"With Citations\": f\"Answer the question using the context. Cite the source at the end.\\n\\nContext: {context}\\nQuestion: {query}\\nAnswer:\",\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "for name, prompt in prompts.items():\n",
    "    response = llm.predict(prompt)\n",
    "    print(f\"--- {name} Prompt ---\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Response: {response}\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Exercise: Improve a Poor Query\n",
    "\n",
    "Try a vague query and see how retrieval fails, then improve it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "vague_query = \"banking rules\"\n",
    "good_query = \"What are the minimum capital requirements for banks under Basel III?\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Vague query results:\")\n",
    "for doc in vector_store.similarity_search(vague_query, k=2):\n",
    "    print(doc.page_content[:100])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nSpecific query results:\")\n",
    "for doc in vector_store.similarity_search(good_query, k=2):\n",
    "    print(doc.page_content[:100])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Putting It All Together: Optimized RAG Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "Here's a function that combines retrieval, re-ranking, and prompt engineering."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def optimized_rag(query: str, use_rerank: bool = True) -> str:\n",
    "    # Retrieve more candidates\n",
    "    candidates = vector_store.similarity_search(query, k=5)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Re-rank\n",
    "    if use_rerank:\n",
    "        top_docs = rerank_with_crossencoder(query, candidates, top_k=2)\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        top_docs = candidates[:2]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    context = \"\\n\".join([doc.page_content for doc in top_docs])\n",
    "    prompt = f\"\"\"You are an AI assistant for financial regulations. \n",
    "Use only the context below to answer the question. \n",
    "If the context doesn't contain the answer, say \"The information is not available in the provided documents.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "Context: {context}\n",
    "\n",
    "Question: {query}\n",
    "Answer:\"\"\"\n",
    "    response = llm.predict(prompt)\n",
    "    return response\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test\n",
    "test_q = \"What is the capital conservation buffer under Basel III?\"\n",
    "print(optimized_rag(test_q, use_rerank=True))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
